This direcory can be builds into a web site using Jekyll
(jekyllrb.com).

Viewing the site locally:

$ jekyll serve --port 8989

Deploying the site to github pages:

Clone the repository into some directory $WEBSITE, check out the
gh-pages branch.

$ pushd some/other/directory
$ git clone https://github.com/Microsoft/ivy.git
$ cd ivy
$ git checkout gh-pages
$ WEBSITE=`pwd`

Copy the contents of this directory into the
clone's root directory:

$ pushd
$ cp -a * $WEBSITE

Now go back to the website directory, commit the changes and push
them:

$ pushd
$ git commit -a -m 'copied from master'
$ git push origin gh-pages

GitHub should automatically update the web site after the push.

There is a script in this directory that will accomplish all of the above:

$ ./deploy






